title: Tocagen's brain cancer treatment fails late-stage study - Nasdaq.com
text: Sept 12 (Reuters) - Tocagen Inc  said on Thursday its experimental treatment did not prove effective in helping patients with a type of brain cancer to live longer, in a late-stage study.
The California-based company said in the trial its lead product candidate Toca 511 & Toca FC also did not show meaningful superiority in secondary goals compared to standard of care treatment.
